  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "This coherence score is then used to determine whether a set number of topics for that data set are semantically interpretable rather than being related only because of statistical inference [61].For this study, we used the Gensim (RARE Technologies Ltd) implementation of LDA topic coherence [62], which is an implementation of a 4-stage topic coherence specified by Röder et al [63].",
    "The results of coherence testing revealed that the models with the highest coherence scores were for a topic model with 19 topics (coherence score=0.481) and 10 topics (coherence score=0.478).",
    "To determine semantic coherence at the human level, a model including the 10 and 19 topics was created using BigML (BigML, Inc).",
    "Manual coherence testing involved visually inspecting the models created through BigML, including the spread of the topics, coherence of the top 10 terms within each topic, and distinction among the different sets of top-10 words within each topic.",
    "BigML displays the topics in a topic map (Figure 2) by plotting topics as circles, with the size of the circle representing the topic probability [64]."
  ],
